steps.description:
Use a sharp serrated knife to cut the squash into quarters lengthwise. Cut the squash in half from top to bottom. Use a sawing motion. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/81/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/81/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut each half in half, again working from top to bottom in a sawing motion. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a8/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a8/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Peeling the squash is not necessary. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a4/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a4/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use a metal spoon or melon-baller to remove the seeds and stringy pulp. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fd/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fd/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Coat the upward-facing, cut-side of each quarter. Drizzle a generous amount of olive oil over each quarter. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/75/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/75/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Divide the butter equally among all the quarters. Dot the cut surface with small chunks of butter. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/ec/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/ec/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Sprinkle salt and pepper over the squash. This should be done according to taste, but if you are uncertain where to start, use roughly 1/4 tsp (1.25 ml) salt and 1/8 tsp (0.62 ml) pepper per quarter. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/45/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/45/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Additional herbs and seasonings can also be used. For instance, you can sprinkle the squash with thyme or parsley for a savory taste or a dash of red pepper for a spicier flavor. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2b/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet4.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/2b/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet4.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Allow the squash to cool slightly before cutting it in half lengthwise. Wait at least 10 to 15 minutes after pulling the squash out of the oven. Otherwise, it might be too hot for you to handle, and you could end up burning your fingers. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/be/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/be/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use a serrated knife to split the squash open from top to bottom. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/00/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/00/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Dig out the seeds and stringy fibers with a metal spoon or melon-baller. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c8/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-10Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-10Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c8/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-10Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-10Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Sprinkle it with salt and pepper, to taste. Use as much salt and pepper as desired. If you are uncertain about how much to use, start with 1/2 tsp (2.5 ml) salt and 1/4 tsp (1.25 ml) pepper per half. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4b/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4b/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If desired, you can also drizzle the halves with melted butter or a little olive oil. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/08/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/08/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":357,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":590.2912621359224,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

For a tangier twist, consider drizzling the squash with lime juice. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/de/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/de/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

To make the squash easier to serve, you may wish to cut the halves in half again, ultimately dividing the squash into quarters. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/47/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet4.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/47/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet4.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-11Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use a vegetable peeler to shave off the peel and a sharp knife to cut the squash into 1-inch (2.5-cm) slices. Cut 1 inch (2.5 cm) from the top and bottom of the squash. Discard pieces. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/af/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/af/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use a serrated vegetable peeler to remove the thick skin until you reveal the orange flesh beneath. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f2/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f2/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use a metal spoon or melon-baller to scoop out the seeds and fibers inside. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6d/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6d/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make width-wise slices, cutting from side to side, that are each about 1 inch (2.5 cm) thick. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ce/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet4.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ce/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet4.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-13Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Drizzle the oil over the baking sheet and directly over the slices. Olive oil works well, but you can also use walnut oil or other types of vegetable oil. Drizzle half of the olive oil over the baking sheet. Dredge each slice in the oil, turning it over so that both sides get covered. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/14/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-14Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-14Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/14/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-14Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-14Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Drizzle the remaining oil directly over each slice. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/52/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-14Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-14Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/52/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-14Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-14Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If desired, you can also spray the slices with cooking spray. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0c/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-14Bullet4.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-14Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0c/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-14Bullet4.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-14Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use a sharp serrated knife to divide the squash in half lengthwise. Cut the squash in half from top to bottom. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9a/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-22Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-22Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9a/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-22Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-22Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Peeling is not necessary or desired. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f5/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-22Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-22Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f5/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-22Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-22Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Scoop out the seeds and pulp with a metal spoon or melon-baller. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d5/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-22Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-22Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d5/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-22Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-22Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If desired, scoop out the softened flesh and place it into a large bowl. Use a potato masher to mash brown sugar, butter, and cinnamon into the squash. Wait several minutes after pulling the squash out of the oven before handling it. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7f/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-26Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-26Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7f/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-26Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-26Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

You can also serve the squash without mashing it. Simply divide the squash into quarters or however many pieces you desire. Sprinkle it with brown sugar, butter, and cinnamon, or try different seasonings, like salt and pepper. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/29/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-26Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-26Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/29/Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-26Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Cook-Butternut-Squash-in-the-Oven-Step-26Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
